cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks on social media text, which is a common topic in the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges of handling noise and linguistic variations in short online posts, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed model is a hybrid word-character attention-based encoder-decoder model, which involves deep learning techniques and can be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
